d Engagement (CODE)&rdquo; Programme, which provided tailor-made training for student officers, were conducted. Since the content of the two core seminars was considered essential to the development of student organizations, the attendance to the two core seminars was made as prerequisite for student organizations who have the need to (1) reserve venues via VFBS in July and August and (2) organize Sales Week in 2018-19.<br />\n<br />\nRecently, requests for help in venue reservation in July and August were received from a few student organizations which did not (or partially) fulfill the attendance requirement. Considering this is the first year to implement CODE with attendance requirements, the Office has resolved to offer remedial measures. Those student organizations who have not fulfilled CODE Attendance requirement would be required to send the following documents to sacla@hkbu.edu.hk on or before 22 June 2018 (Friday):<br />\n<br />\n1. A note to student organizations which have completed the CODE Programme, to explain with justifications or confession for not fulfilling the requirement; and<br />\n<br />\n2. A summary of no less than 1,000 words for EACH core seminar the student organization has missed. The Powerpoint slides could be viewed via the website (HKBU login required)<br />\n<br />\nCompleting the two documents with satisfactory level before the deadline would be regarded as completion of CODE requirement. Please note that no further arrangement would be provided for late submission. If your student organization were having a similar case, same measure would apply.<br />\n<br />\nKindly be advised that the remedial measure is offered to this transitional year only. Student organizations are recommended to ensure messages from the Office are well received and due action is taken.<br />\n<br />\nPlease contact Mr. Cliff WONG at 3411 2567 or via email cliffwong@hkbu.edu.hk for any queries.<br />\n<br />\nCampus Life and Amenities<br />\n<br />\nOffice